      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "This issue often indicates a failed capacitor, a dirty condenser coil causing airflow problems, or a tripped safety thermal switch. Due to the risk of high-voltage shock from any residual power in the capacitor and the possibility of sharp metal edges, it is generally **not safe** for you to inspect the unit yourself without turning off the main breaker first. I highly recommend calling a certified HVAC technician to diagnose and repair the problem safely.",
